WEBVTT

00:06.466 --> 00:08.594
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:54.700 --> 01:55.784
(ECHOING MOANS)

01:58.620 --> 01:59.705
(GASPS)

02:13.552 --> 02:15.971
- CHLOE: What's out there?
- You scared me.

02:16.888 --> 02:20.642
Gonna have to tie a bell around your neck
so you don't keep sneaking up on me.

02:20.726 --> 02:22.561
What do you look at in the ocean?

02:24.062 --> 02:25.272
Oh, nothing.

02:26.565 --> 02:29.109
You spend a lot of time staring at "nothing."

02:31.236 --> 02:32.571
Okay, I take it back.

02:33.405 --> 02:36.908
It's something, it's the big "out there."

02:38.493 --> 02:42.748
The ocean is powerful, but mostly it's vast.

02:45.083 --> 02:47.127
It's full of life, mystery.

02:48.587 --> 02:51.465
Who knows what lies out there
beneath the surface?

02:52.424 --> 02:55.761
- CHLOE: Monsters?
- Monsters? Maybe.

02:56.678 --> 02:59.097
Dreams, sunken treasure.

03:01.266 --> 03:04.436
It's the great unknown.
That's what the ocean is.

03:07.773 --> 03:09.441
<i>ZIGGY: I don't want to go, Mom.</i>

03:10.025 --> 03:11.818
I know you don't, but you have to.

03:12.778 --> 03:13.987
It's gonna be fine.

03:14.112 --> 03:15.947
They all think I choked that girl.

03:16.114 --> 03:18.784
Yeah, but you know that you didn't
and I know that you didn't.

03:19.117 --> 03:21.453
And it's good enough for me.
It should be good enough for you.

03:21.536 --> 03:24.289
It's gonna be good enough
for everyone else, too.

03:27.042 --> 03:28.460
What's our mantra?

03:29.461 --> 03:30.629
Every day, we're gonna be...

03:31.797 --> 03:32.964
- Brave.
- So brave.

03:33.048 --> 03:34.299
Good job. Let's go.

03:35.050 --> 03:37.302
ZIGGY: Mom. Why did we move here?

03:37.636 --> 03:38.678
Ziggy-

03:43.517 --> 03:44.559
Okay.

03:47.229 --> 03:50.482
I don't have time for this this morning.
Please put your shirt on.

03:50.816 --> 03:52.567
Why did we move here?

03:55.320 --> 03:57.155
- Why?
- That's enough.

04:01.535 --> 04:03.245
You can finish that in the car. Let's go.

04:05.705 --> 04:08.083
I don't mean to do your job
but it begs the question,

04:08.333 --> 04:09.751
"Is she running from something?"

04:09.835 --> 04:11.962
You cannot be serious, Joseph.

04:12.045 --> 04:13.255
(SOUL MUSIC PLAYING)

04:13.422 --> 04:14.506
What?

04:15.173 --> 04:16.216
No.

04:16.882 --> 04:18.802
No, this makes us look like cowards.

04:18.885 --> 04:20.553
If you roll over on this, it sets a precedent...

04:20.678 --> 04:23.181
<i>- JOSEPH: He basically laughed.
- Do not yell at me!</i>

04:23.682 --> 04:25.934
- They <i>don't</i> know.
- You're the one... Honey, can you...

04:26.017 --> 04:27.769
<i>If I go talk to the mayor,
he might consider legal...</i>

04:27.853 --> 04:29.896
