So, you know, I kind of expect her
to be rough on me,

35:00.976 --> 35:04.020
but I think it's...
Like, you can't punish Bonnie.

35:05.647 --> 35:09.818
Well, I believe she's being nice to Bonnie,
or at least trying, under the circumstances.

35:12.153 --> 35:14.072
What circumstances would those be?

35:14.572 --> 35:17.158
Nathan, come on.
It was pretty tough when you left.

35:18.910 --> 35:20.704
What? That was like 15 years ago.

35:22.914 --> 35:28.128
It's difficult for Madeline to see you
at every school function, so involved,

35:28.211 --> 35:31.006
when you weren't there for Abigail.

35:31.589 --> 35:33.842
It's difficult to run into you at yoga
when you never...

35:34.718 --> 35:36.636
You know what?
Maybe I'm talking out of turn here.

35:36.720 --> 35:38.596
No. I was young. You know?

35:39.723 --> 35:41.391
And maybe a bit of a shit.

35:42.434 --> 35:45.061
And I made some real mistakes
with both Maddie and Abby.

35:45.729 --> 35:48.273
But should I be required to make
the same mistakes with Bonnie and Skye?

35:48.398 --> 35:52.944
No. But, you know, it doesn't hurt to be
mindful of other people's feelings sometimes.

35:53.361 --> 35:55.405
Oh, yeah, yeah. Mr. Sensitive.

35:56.531 --> 35:57.615
Excuse me?

35:57.866 --> 36:00.076
No, actually, I meant that as a compliment.

36:01.578 --> 36:04.372
You're kind of like today's
standard bearer for the evolved man.

36:04.748 --> 36:06.249
Like you work at home, and you...

36:06.374 --> 36:08.710
And you do almost 50-50 of the child care.
You even cook.

36:08.793 --> 36:12.839
So you're the guy who likes to
fish and hunt, and I'm...

36:12.922 --> 36:14.591
- Mr. Girly-man?
- That's not what I meant at all, man.

36:14.716 --> 36:16.885
Listen, I thought it'd be indelicate
to bring it up with Maddie.

36:16.968 --> 36:18.553
That's why I'm bringing it up with you.

36:19.888 --> 36:22.766
Well, that sounded like a threat, Nathan.
Are you threatening me?

36:23.266 --> 36:25.935
No, but actually, I feel like
you're starting to threaten me,

36:26.061 --> 36:28.063
which I don't think you want to go there.

36:31.858 --> 36:35.779
You know, this thing with that Ziggy kid,
all the talk of bullying?

36:37.947 --> 36:38.948
I was bullied.

36:39.449 --> 36:40.533
Sixth grade.

36:40.617 --> 36:43.620
And I always turned the other cheek,

36:43.745 --> 36:46.539
thinking that was
the more mature thing to do.

36:49.084 --> 36:51.920
Some 30 years later, it still haunts me

36:52.879 --> 36:55.799
that I didn't beat the shit out of that kid.

36:56.591 --> 36:59.219
So much so, I find myself fantasizing

36:59.928 --> 37:04.057
that somebody will come along
one day and say or do something to me,

37:05.934 --> 37:08.144
that'll offer me the chance to redeem myself.

37:12.148 --> 37:13.983
You've always treated me quite well, Nathan.

37:15.402 --> 37:16.611
It's too bad.

37:20.907 --> 37:22.117
Too bad.

37:27.831 --> 37:28.915
(SCOFFS)

37:30.083 --> 37:32.585
The first thing I said,
the very first thing I said,

37:32.669 --> 37:33.962
it wasn't just the mothers.

37:35.839 --> 37:38.425
I'm gonna kick your fuckin' ass,
you fuckin' talk to me like that again,

37:38.508 --> 37:39.759
you fuckin' little shit.

37:40.343 --> 37:43.847
Ed and Nathan hated each other's guts.
Are we all afraid to say that?

37:43.972 --> 37:46.141
<i>There's clearly a lot of
bad blood in this community.</i>

37:56.860 --> 37:57.944
MADELINE: <i>What did he say?</i>

37:58.027 --> 38:00.864
<i>JOSEPH: The mayor refuses to
authorize funding for the production.</i>

38:00.989 --> 38:03.950
MADELINE: <i>Well, it should be a legal matter
and we could make it a legal matter.</i>

38:04.033 --> 38:06.369
The funding is discretionary.
He could deny it on whatever grounds...

38:06.661 --> 38:07.704
Is he denying it?

38:07.829 --> 38:10.457
He's suggesting we pick
something more community-centric.

38:10.540 --> 38:13.042
Joseph, we have worked so hard for this.

38:13.168 --> 38:16.296
And we are being victimized
by the small-mindedness

38:16.379 --> 38:18.715
led by the likes of Renata Klein.

38:18.798 --> 38:21.217
Understood, but we need to pick our battles.
And this is just...

38:21.342 --> 38:24.387
And, sometimes, our battles pick us.

38:24.512 --> 38:26.723
We can't quit. We just can't.

38:28.725 --> 38:30.852
Is this about the play, or winning?

38:31.895 --> 38:32.979
(SCOFFS)

38:33.897 --> 38:36.024
I don't know. Maybe it's a little bit about both.

38:36.566 --> 38:37.734
But I get sick and tired

38:37.817 --> 38:41.154
of the morally superior in this town
stepping all over everybody else.

38:41.696 --> 38:44.407
And you said you wanted to be brave
with your artistic direction.

38:44.532 --> 38:45.700
That's all I'm asking.

38:45.992 --> 38:47.035
Just...

38:47.243 --> 38:48.745
Just be brave.

38:51.164 --> 38:53.082
You told me to go fuck myself on the head.

38:53.249 --> 38:54.250
(LAUGHS)

38:55.502 --> 38:59.047
I just get... You know how I get.

39:00.006 --> 39:01.049
(CHUCKLES)

39:02.008 --> 39:04.761
Please, this is important to me.

39:07.347 --> 39:09.724
- I'll talk to the Mayor.
-(SIGHS) Thank you.

39:10.099 --> 39:12.685
You're not gonna regret it. You're not.

39:14.896 --> 39:16.022
What's this?

39:16.105 --> 39:19.108
JOSEPH: Frozen.
I'm taking my wife and my little niece.

39:21.736 --> 39:24.781
Amabella passed out her invitations
on Wednesday morning.

39:24.864 --> 39:28.785
Madeline was on the phone inviting
the kids to Disney On <i>Ice,</i> by Thursday noon.

39:29.285 --> 39:32.288
<i>HARPER: The two events were scheduled
for the same day, same time.</i>

39:32.413 --> 39:33.748
A vicious shot over the bow.

39:33.873 --> 39:34.916
(WHINES)

39:35.416 --> 39:36.751
HARPER: Yeah. It's ridiculous.

39:38.419 --> 39:41.297
- Okay. Thank you.
- Yeah. Of course.

39:41.422 --> 39:42.966
I mean, I don't know
what's wrong with this woman.

39:43.091 --> 39:45.802
It's like she's power hungry,
she can't just let us all get along...

39:45.885 --> 39:47.470
(SCREAMING) <i>I</i> said, "Thank you!"

39:47.595 --> 39:48.805
(SCREAMING)

39:52.225 --> 39:54.310
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

40:28.136 --> 40:30.179
(PHONE VIBRATING)

40:34.267 --> 40:35.310
Hello?

40:36.603 --> 40:38.688
(PANTING)

40:40.857 --> 40:43.192
<i>JANE: Sexual assault?</i>

40:43.318 --> 40:46.696
<i>PRINCIPAL NIPPAL:
It appears Ziggy kissed Amabella.</i>

40:46.821 --> 40:49.866
<i>Ziggy's advance was unwelcome
and a little aggressive.</i>

40:52.368 --> 40:54.954
<i>(ECHOING) Ziggy kissed Amabella.</i>

40:55.038 --> 40:56.122
(PHONE RINGS)

40:56.956 --> 41:00.460
<i>(ECHOING) Ziggy kissed Amabella.</i>

41:01.878 --> 41:04.047
<i>In addition to the murder investigation,</i>

41:04.172 --> 41:09.010
<i>we are investigating others on assault
and conspiracy to incite violence.</i>

41:09.719 --> 41:13.890
The intent, by all accounts,
was to simply make peace with Amabella.

41:14.140 --> 41:16.643
Which is an admission
that he did try to choke her.

41:16.726 --> 41:18.061
No, just hold on.

41:18.895 --> 41:21.731
Zigfield still maintains his innocence
on the whole choking front.

41:22.190 --> 41:26.069
The idea of brandishing affection
upon Amabella was first proffered by Chloe

41:26.194 --> 41:28.321
in an attempt to ameliorate
the birthday party brouhaha.

41:28.404 --> 41:31.032
I'm sorry, excuse me. Are you saying
Chloe had something to do with this?

41:31.199 --> 41:32.241
- Yes.
- RENATA: Yes.

41:32.325 --> 41:33.368
Mrs Klein.

41:35.495 --> 41:38.915
She played a song. She invited
Zigfield and Amabella to dance.

41:40.875 --> 41:42.335
And it seems your daughter has inherited the

41:42.418 --> 41:44.253
-"Let's solve everyone else's problems" gene.
-(SCOFFS)

41:44.379 --> 41:46.506
The motion was then seconded by Skye.

41:46.589 --> 41:49.592
I don't believe that my daughter would ever
sanction a non-consensual touching.

41:49.717 --> 41:51.594
She's a very peaceful child.

41:51.719 --> 41:54.347
Isn't this just a lot of brouhaha
about nothing?

41:54.430 --> 41:56.766
Well, look, we have a policy, sir,
and we'll get to the bottom of it.

41:56.891 --> 41:58.267
- RENATA: Really? You have a policy?
- Yes.

41:58.393 --> 41:59.602
RENATA: Well, isn't that great news?

41:59.727 --> 42:02.105
